div.div: Results of twenty randomly selected Monte Carlo trials.
div.p: Each line represents the relative biomass trajectory of that species over the course of a single trial. Note that the starting value for all species is one, and model results is relative to that value. Also Note that the y-axis scales for N. rossii and C. gunnari are two to three orders of magnitude larger than the scales for the other species, indicating much higher sensitivity and uncertainty for these two species.
